The paper deals with generalization bounds for deep neural networks, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically mentions convolutional neural networks (cs.CV) and discusses the compression of trained networks, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces new noise stability properties of deep nets, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses a compression-based framework to derive its results, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
